    },
    {
      "id": "Vwsn-MVNlRXSZQ39mErMx",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -2404.319794808458,
      "y": -6466.917667737615,
      "width": 868.6994018554688,
      "height": 425,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 90,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bBf",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2068286306,
      "version": 741,
      "versionNonce": 1762771326,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1770470913281,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "HLD:\n1. rate limiting on basis of clients and rules:\n\nThree solutions where to keep the rate limiter: in process, dedicated service\nand api gateway\n\n   1.  client -> gateway -> service (multiple nodes)\n\n    It is only fine if approximate limits and #Nodes==1.\n    Benefit is really fast.\n\n   2. client -> gateway -> service (connected to another rate limiting service)\n\n    The benefit is one can tune what information and rules are needed. More \n    customization can be done. The main issue is its one more service maintenance, which \n    is an overkill. Second network hops takes its own sweet time.\n  ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "HLD:\n1. rate limiting on basis of clients and rules:\n\nThree solutions where to keep the rate limiter: in process, dedicated service\nand api gateway\n\n   1.  client -> gateway -> service (multiple nodes)\n\n    It is only fine if approximate limits and #Nodes==1.\n    Benefit is really fast.\n\n   2. client -> gateway -> service (connected to another rate limiting service)\n\n    The benefit is one can tune what information and rules are needed. More \n    customization can be done. The main issue is its one more service maintenance, which \n    is an overkill. Second network hops takes its own sweet time.\n  ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "q1bKuQuuYhuDLltYXFWzr",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -2382.702564865275,
      "y": -6033.4350336219995,
      "width": 823.939453125,
      "height": 75,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 90,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bBg",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 920760994,
      "version": 191,
      "versionNonce": 440165154,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1770470907839,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "3. use in api gateway\nMost efficient appraoch to go with. It lies on edge. The main issue is customization\nlike that premium users should get 10x more limits, else it is fine.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "3. use in api gateway\nMost efficient appraoch to go with. It lies on edge. The main issue is customization\nlike that premium users should get 10x more limits, else it is fine.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
