    {
      "id": "TGMj68DcgxCguEaHGAUym",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -2305.8703050516838,
      "y": -5649.628443750296,
      "width": 977.5394287109375,
      "height": 300,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 90,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bBm",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 604584638,
      "version": 741,
      "versionNonce": 888948706,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1770471577333,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "There are different algos which can be talked about in LLD round as well:\n1. fixed window: the main issue is edge calls. It leads to starvation to other users. \nImplement using hashmap of clientId, counter and last timestamp that is it\n\n2. sliding window log: store the timestamp of each request. use priority queue for \nevicting the older timestamps. \nOne can keep the queue with client id mapping, that queue is being emptied on the basis \nof new request coming in LLD\n\n3. sliding window counter: Keeps two counters per client, get the allowed requests on how much time\nhas been spent on the current minute.\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "There are different algos which can be talked about in LLD round as well:\n1. fixed window: the main issue is edge calls. It leads to starvation to other users. \nImplement using hashmap of clientId, counter and last timestamp that is it\n\n2. sliding window log: store the timestamp of each request. use priority queue for \nevicting the older timestamps. \nOne can keep the queue with client id mapping, that queue is being emptied on the basis \nof new request coming in LLD\n\n3. sliding window counter: Keeps two counters per client, get the allowed requests on how much time\nhas been spent on the current minute.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
